INTEGER DATA TYPES:
byte 8 bit e.g. byte centuries = 20;
short 16 bit e.g. short years = 2000;
int 32 bit e.g. int days = 9384983;
long 64 bit e.g. long hours = 389302393984;

Minimize the amount of memory you  are using by picking data types which can save lower values 

Pound to Dollars: 

Scanner scanner - new Scanner(System.in);
double pounds = scanner.nextDouble();

double dollars = pounds * 1.31;

System.out.printlnf("%.3f%n", dollars);

Implict type conversion: variable of bigger type take smaller value 
e.g. 
float heightInMeters = 1.74f;
double maxHeight = heightInMeters;

Explicit type conversion: precision is lost  

BOOLEAN DATA TYPE: variables that hold true or false

CHARACTER DATA TYPE: char keyword

STRING DATA TYPE
